A RESOLUTION
1 Congratulating Leo Mazzone upon his induction into the Georgia Sports Hall of Fame; and
2 for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, the Georgia Sports Hall of Fame has recently announced its Class of 2025
4 inductees, with the 69th Annual Induction Ceremony set to take place on February 21 and
5 22, 2025, in Macon, Georgia; and
6 WHEREAS, Leo Mazzone, one of the most influential pitching coaches in Major League
7 Baseball history, has been selected for induction into the Georgia Sports Hall of Fame in
8 recognition of his extraordinary contributions to the sport; and
9 WHEREAS, he served as the Atlanta Braves' pitching coach from 1990 to 2005,
10 orchestrating one of the most dominant pitching rotations in baseball history and mentoring
11 Hall of Famers Greg Maddux, Tom Glavine, and John Smoltz to sustained excellence; and
12 WHEREAS, under his leadership, the Braves secured 14 consecutive division titles and
13 captured the 1995 World Series, earning its well-deserved reputation as one of the most
14 successful franchises of the era; and
